WEBVTT

00:03.562 --> 00:04.839
So he still has the bike?

00:05.004 --> 00:06.650
He promises weekends only,

00:06.674 --> 00:08.681
and then on Friday, he rides it to work.

00:08.724 --> 00:10.704
He says that's the start of the weekend.

00:10.728 --> 00:11.903
So you get pregnant,

00:11.927 --> 00:13.363
he goes back to being an adrenaline junkie.

00:13.387 --> 00:15.088
Yeah, that's who he
is, which is frustrating

00:15.112 --> 00:16.934
because he's obviously happy.

00:16.958 --> 00:19.084
What is this, 1950? Clearly,<i>
you're</i> not happy.

00:19.108 --> 00:21.257
Bozo went B.A.S.E.
jumping two weekends ago.

00:21.281 --> 00:23.839
Okay, he went parasailing
strapped to the back of an A.T.V.

00:23.863 --> 00:25.057
I mean, really, who does that?

00:25.081 --> 00:26.967
- So tell him to stop.
- I can't do that.

00:26.991 --> 00:29.646
He loves that stuff. I mean...

00:29.670 --> 00:30.693
He will resent me.

00:30.717 --> 00:33.347
And I know I would resent
him if he tried to change me.

00:33.371 --> 00:35.130
But you're not risking your life.

00:35.154 --> 00:37.104
He has to be more
responsible to you, right?

00:37.127 --> 00:40.329
I agree. But... it's the man that
I fell in love with, you know?

00:40.353 --> 00:41.438
It's what made him different

00:41.462 --> 00:42.638
from the other guys I was dating.

00:42.662 --> 00:45.696
Which is fine if you are <i> dating,</i>
but now he's gonna be a father.

00:45.719 --> 00:47.405
I think there... there has
to be a middle ground, huh?

00:47.429 --> 00:48.761
- Yeah. We're still trying to find it.
- We're on it.

00:48.785 --> 00:50.318
Gwen, M.V.A. in Prospect Hill.

00:50.342 --> 00:51.667
Auto versus auto sounds bad.

00:51.691 --> 00:53.133
Okay, I'm on it. See ya. Catch you later.

00:53.157 --> 00:54.455
Hey, what are you doing
here? Isn't it your night off?

00:54.479 --> 00:55.885
Yeah. I wanna go on a ride-along with you.

00:55.909 --> 00:57.454
No. I'm serious.

00:57.478 --> 00:58.563
Look, I already got Topher's permission.

00:58.587 --> 01:00.541
- I just need yours now.
- Why do you wanna do this?

01:00.565 --> 01:01.440
'Cause I'm the new charge nurse,

01:01.464 --> 01:02.614
but I don't feel much in charge yet.

01:02.638 --> 01:04.232
I wanna experience what
happens to the patients

01:04.256 --> 01:05.272
before they come to us.

01:05.297 --> 01:07.343
Careful what you wish for.
It can get crazy out there.

01:07.367 --> 01:09.038
Anything goes down, I'll
be there to protect you.

01:09.062 --> 01:11.188
Oh, honey, I've seen things
that'll make you wet your pants.

01:11.212 --> 01:12.348
I'm ready for anything.

01:12.372 --> 01:13.397
Just make sure you don't slow me down.

01:13.421 --> 01:14.982
- All right? Get in there.
- Ha ha! Yes!

01:16.000 --> 01:22.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:28.327 --> 01:30.863
Whoa! Watch out for lives wires!

01:33.728 --> 01:34.858
Yeah, be careful.

01:39.732 --> 01:40.976
What do we got?

01:41.000 --> 01:43.886
We got one female with a leg
laceration. Right over there.

01:43.910 --> 01:45.574
- Shane! Shane!
- Hey.

01:45.598 --> 01:46.653
- Oh, my God!
- Okay.

01:46.677 --> 01:49.107
Shane! Uh, y-you have
to go help my boyfriend.

01:49.131 --> 01:50.276
He's trapped under there.

01:50.300 --> 01:51.675
- The thing came crashing down on him.
- All right,

01:51.699 --> 01:52.711
just take it... just calm down.

01:52.735 --> 01:54.113
- Let me take a look at this.
- Shane?

01:54.136 --> 01:56.510
- Just be patient, please. Everything's gonna be okay.
- Okay.

01:56.534 --> 01:58.639
- What's your name?
- M-my name's Lindsay.

01:58.663 --> 02:00.383
All right, Lindsay, anything else hurt?

02:00.407 --> 02:01.934
- No, just my leg.
- Okay.

02:06.754 --> 02:08.872
Oh, Lordy. You see that ride?

02:08.896 --> 02:11.199
You saw that ride, didn't
you? Oh, man!

02:11.223 --> 02:13.105
You've been impaled. Don't move.

02:13.129 --> 02:14.639
- Oh, well, so I have.
- Yeah.

02:14.663 --> 02:16.172
- I'm Shane McCoy.
- Yeah?

02:16.196 --> 02:18.070
Yeah. You seen me ride
out there, didn't you?

02:18.094 --> 02:20.079
- Okay, hold still. Okay?
- It was a shame the way it ended, though.

02:20.103 --> 02:22.131
I could've ridden that
bull till sunset, you know.

02:22.155 --> 02:24.141
- Okay, okay. I-I need you to stop talking, okay?
- I'd-a had my 8 seconds, too.

02:24.165 --> 02:25.754
You lost a lot of blood.
Your heart is racing.

02:25.778 --> 02:26.986
- Yeah.
- I'm gonna push this off you.

02:27.009 --> 02:28.055
- On three.
- Okay.

02:28.079 --> 02:29.302
Okay, one...

02:29.327 --> 02:30.846
Two... Three.

02:44.783 --> 02:46.734
- Shane!
- Tee!

02:46.758 --> 02:48.273
Ohh!

02:48.297 --> 02:50.191
Whoa, ho!

02:50.215 --> 02:51.654
What a rush, huh?

02:51.678 --> 02:53.746
What a rush! What a rush!

02:53.770 --> 02:55.461
That's bull ridin', son.

02:55.485 --> 02:57.387
- Yeah.
- Never felt so alive.

02:57.411 --> 02:59.163
- That was something.
- Yeah!

02:59.187 --> 03:00.949
Tee!

03:00.973 --> 03:02.572
- Holy...
- Close call.

03:02.596 --> 03:04.977
Just... Be careful.

03:05.506 --> 03:09.005
High time we got this started. Thank you.

03:09.495 --> 03:10.772
- Hey, Topher.
- Oh. Hey.

03:10.796 --> 03:12.752
Um, I just wanted to make sure
that you got my application

03:12.776 --> 03:15.334
- for my second year...
- Chief resident track. Got yours and Paul's.

03:15.358 --> 03:17.239
Too bad there's only one
slot for the two of you.

03:17.263 --> 03:19.405
Aah! Aah!

03:19.429 --> 03:20.551
What's this all about?

03:20.575 --> 03:22.284
- Oh, Ragosa's taking his medical boards next week...
- Warn me first!

03:22.308 --> 03:24.289
And they hooked him up to a
neurostimulator to quiz him.

03:24.313 --> 03:25.879
- Savages.
- No, it's his idea.

03:25.903 --> 03:27.525
- He wanted the motivation.
- You wanna be a big swinging doctor,

03:27.549 --> 03:29.050
- you gotta handle the pressure.
- Aah! Let's do this!

03:29.074 --> 03:31.760
Okay, okay. Um, 10 causes
of pancreatitis. Go!

03:31.784 --> 03:33.286
Gallstones, ethanol, trauma,

03:33.310 --> 03:34.395
- drugs, mumps...
- Faster!

03:34.419 --> 03:35.493
Mumps... aah!

03:36.429 --> 03:38.218
Uh... Steroids, autoimmune,

03:38.242 --> 03:39.584
hyperlipids aah!

03:39.608 --> 03:41.749
- Hey, I was right!
- Sorry, I slipped.

03:41.773 --> 03:42.845
Ohh.

03:42.869 --> 03:43.782
Idiopathic...

03:43.806 --> 03:46.172
You got that look in
your eyes. Don't do it.

03:46.196 --> 03:47.701
No. No, don't do it!

03:47.725 --> 03:48.754
Ow!

03:48.778 --> 03:50.472
You had it on high, didn't you?

03:50.496 --> 03:51.897
- Hey, Topher?
- Scorpion stings.

03:51.921 --> 03:53.650
- I knew that.
- Yeah?

03:53.697 --> 03:55.232
Okay, next one.

03:55.256 --> 03:56.365
Okay, thanks.

03:56.389 --> 03:58.134
Okay, people! Fun's over.

03:58.158 --> 04:00.374
Multiple trauma coming in
from the rodeo. Let's be ready.

04:00.397 --> 04:01.766
All right, I'll take incoming in Trauma 4.

04:01.790 --> 04:03.385
Ragosa, Mollie, get rooms ready!

04:03.409 --> 04:05.671
- Ready on high.
- Double-time, people! Let's go!

04:07.734 --> 04:09.300
- Hey, did you see that?
- Hey!

04:09.324 --> 04:11.680
- Hey, what are you doing?
- Paramedic coming through! Make a way.

04:11.704 --> 04:13.325
- Make a way. Back up, please. Make a path. Make a path.
- What are you doing?

04:13.349 --> 04:15.481
- Get off of him. Everybody, please, step back!
- Give us some room here!

04:15.505 --> 04:18.108
- I'm not gonna tell you again. Get off my son!
- Where's the driver?

04:18.132 --> 04:20.779
- Here's over here! Hurry! Move!
- I'm not gonna tell you again before I kick your ass!

04:20.803 --> 04:23.725
- I'm gonna need you to step back.
- He's the one who hit my boy! He was the driver!

04:23.749 --> 04:24.953
- Calm down. Calm down.
- Sir, I'm a paramedic.

04:24.977 --> 04:26.054
- I'm gonna need you to step aside, okay?
- Step back.

04:26.078 --> 04:30.254
- Hey, buddy, come on. Let her work. Let her work.
- Sir, I'm not gonna tell you twice!

04:30.278 --> 04:31.687
Scott?

04:51.006 --> 04:52.379
- Did you see that?!
- So messed up!

04:52.403 --> 04:54.362
- He's barely breathing.
- Dr. Scott, you are bleeding.

04:54.386 --> 04:55.618
And we gotta get him out of here now!

04:55.642 --> 04:57.868
Look, I'm not gonna tell you again!

04:57.892 --> 04:59.276
Take your hands off my boy!

04:59.300 --> 05:01.766
Get that under control,
all right?! Calm down.

05:01.790 --> 05:04.956
What are you doing? That
man should be in jail!

05:04.989 --> 05:06.428
- Calm down.
- Hey, look, man!

05:06.461 --> 05:07.845
Hey, Kenny! Kenny! Kenny! I got this.

05:07.869 --> 05:10.283
Listen to me carefully, 'cause
I'm only gonna say this once.

05:10.307 --> 05:12.461
That man is a doctor.
You want your son to live?

05:12.485 --> 05:13.926
- Okay. One...
- You let us work, let us get to the hospital.

05:13.950 --> 05:15.795
- Two... Three!
- It is that simple. Is that clear?

05:15.819 --> 05:17.962
He hit my boy.

05:17.986 --> 05:20.066
And now he's trying to help.

05:20.090 --> 05:21.128
Okay?

05:21.152 --> 05:23.078
Hey, I'm gonna need a
statement from the driver.

05:23.108 --> 05:24.869
- Can it wait for the hospital?
- Let's go! Let's go!

05:24.893 --> 05:26.163
- Clear a path!
- Let's go!

05:26.187 --> 05:27.319
- Ready?
- All right, step back.

05:27.343 --> 05:29.626
- One... Two... Three.
- What are you doing?

05:29.650 --> 05:31.499
- Send his ass to jail!
- Watch the equipment.

05:31.523 --> 05:33.727
- Let's go! Let's go! Get moving! Good.
- Okay. All right, make a path! Make a path!

05:33.751 --> 05:34.999
- Back up! Make a way!
- Come on! Come on!

05:35.023 --> 05:36.325
- Hey, calm down! Calm down! Calm down.
- I gotta go with my boy!

05:36.348 --> 05:37.741
Coming through!

05:37.764 --> 05:39.302
All right, people, let's move!

05:39.326 --> 05:41.692
Male, 40s, sever puncture
wounds to the lower flanks,

05:41.716 --> 05:42.908
severe bleeding, possible brain trauma.

05:42.932 --> 05:44.565
- Man's a champ! Saved my...
- Yeah, sit back, sir.

05:44.589 --> 05:46.982
Okay, hang 2 units of O-neg
and send off a trauma panel.

05:47.006 --> 05:48.763
Mollie, bring him to
Trauma 4 and notify C.T.

05:48.787 --> 05:50.942
- Shane? How is he?
- Yeah, still talking.

05:50.966 --> 05:52.742
Female, 40s, deep leg lac, stable.

05:52.766 --> 05:55.141
Hey, nice work, Drew. Curtain
1. Let's get Shane taken care of.

05:55.165 --> 05:56.486
- Someone's feeling energetic.
- Yeah, you know,

05:56.510 --> 05:57.606
you're out in the field,
you're always up, right?

05:57.630 --> 05:59.014
Tee, I'm sorry to pull you off your case.

05:59.038 --> 06:00.348
- I need you on incoming.
- Okay.

06:00.382 --> 06:01.883
Okay, Jordan, you're
with Drew on the cowboy.

06:01.907 --> 06:02.909
- Got it.
- Catch you later, Jordan.

06:02.933 --> 06:04.787
Hey, enjoy that rodeo vic.
He's a real piece of work.

06:04.811 --> 06:06.985
What's up? Scott got in an accident.

06:07.009 --> 06:08.192
- I need you to step in.
- Male, 20s,

06:08.216 --> 06:10.342
blunt chest trauma from
M.V.A., tachy and hypotensive.

06:10.366 --> 06:11.621
Flail chest, probable hemothorax.

06:11.645 --> 06:12.838
Trauma for a chest
tube, then up to the O.R.

06:12.862 --> 06:15.132
- Okay, Tee, go.
- No, no, no! This is my patient!

06:15.166 --> 06:17.029
- No, I'm...
- Wait, Scott! Scott! The police called.

06:17.053 --> 06:18.364
You were <i> in</i> that accident.

06:18.398 --> 06:19.845
Yes, I was, but I'm fine. Topher, I'm fine.

06:19.869 --> 06:21.542
Okay, well, you're gonna
have to answer some questions.

06:21.566 --> 06:23.174
I mean, they need you to take a drug test.

06:23.198 --> 06:25.286
- What happened out there?
- I-I don't can we talk about it later?

06:25.310 --> 06:26.824
No. Okay, fine,

06:26.848 --> 06:29.253
- but there's no way I can let you work on that kid.
- Look, there's no time for this!

06:29.277 --> 06:30.630
The kid needs me in there right now!

06:30.654 --> 06:32.028
Well, not until we check you out.

06:32.061 --> 06:33.253
We gotta make sure there's no brain trauma.

06:33.277 --> 06:34.458
My name is Scott Clemmens.

06:34.482 --> 06:36.662
- Z, y, x, w, v, u, t.
- Scott...

06:36.686 --> 06:38.503
It is Tuesday night at 8:30 P.M.

06:38.527 --> 06:41.628
- That boy's blood pressure is 82 over 42 and falling fast.
- Okay.

06:41.661 --> 06:42.844
I am the on-call surgeon,

06:42.878 --> 06:44.134
and if you don't let me in there right now

06:44.158 --> 06:46.021
to drain the blood from
his chest, he's gonna die.

06:46.045 --> 06:47.740
Okay, look, T.C. can get it started.

06:47.764 --> 06:49.522
We can call around for
another thoracic surgeon.

06:49.546 --> 06:51.825
Oh, come on! Just...

06:51.849 --> 06:54.867
Do the neuro, clear me,
and let me get into surgery.

06:54.891 --> 06:56.401
Scott, even if...

06:56.991 --> 06:59.006
The... the family has called the hospital.

06:59.037 --> 07:01.051
They don't want you
anywhere near their son.

07:01.213 --> 07:04.260
I'm sorry, you're gonna
have to sit this one out.

07:04.284 --> 07:05.757
Well, actually, you know,

07:05.781 --> 07:07.860
it's not as dangerous
as people think it is.

07:07.884 --> 07:09.673
- Bandage, please.
- Ain't no rules, no nothing.

07:09.697 --> 07:10.885
You know oh!

07:10.909 --> 07:13.148
You're hotter than a summer revival.

07:13.181 --> 07:13.922
Amen.

07:13.946 --> 07:15.645
Easy there, cowboy.
She's already spoken for.

07:15.669 --> 07:17.395
Man's gotta speak his mind.

07:17.419 --> 07:18.551
Hey, you better speak it quieter.

07:18.575 --> 07:20.550
- Your girlfriend's in the next room.
- Yeah. How is she?

07:20.574 --> 07:22.011
- She's good.
- All right.

07:22.046 --> 07:23.421
I sutured the wound, but he's still tachy.

07:23.445 --> 07:25.555
Blood infusion could help.
What about his X-rays?

07:25.610 --> 07:28.201
- Uh, they're right over there. They look normal to me.
- Okay.

07:28.225 --> 07:29.983
Where's Dr. Superman at?

07:30.007 --> 07:31.460
I need to give him a hug.

07:31.484 --> 07:33.738
I'd be feedin' the worms
if he hadn't come along.

07:33.762 --> 07:35.027
Talking about T.C.

07:35.051 --> 07:38.652
Oh, boy, talk about cojones.
He nearly gave up the ghost.

07:38.686 --> 07:41.596
- I'm sorry. What?
- You know, died.

07:41.629 --> 07:44.594
This giant silver thingamabob,
sharper than a spur,

07:44.618 --> 07:47.181
- it came down about this close to his neck.
- Is that true?

07:48.920 --> 07:50.999
I guess. I don't know. I mean, I was...

07:51.023 --> 07:52.394
- came in from a bad angle.
- Drew.

07:52.418 --> 07:53.862
Bad angle? What are you talking about?

07:53.886 --> 07:55.782
This thing, it would've cut his
head, I swear to God. All right!

07:55.806 --> 07:57.618
Come down and
punctured him! It was right there!

07:57.619 --> 07:59.297
- Sir, just breathe deep.

07:59.321 --> 08:01.765
- Drew?
- Blood would've been everywhere. I was sittin' right next to him.

08:01.789 --> 08:03.707
- Does this hurt?
- Mnh-mnh.

08:03.731 --> 08:05.361
- All right, what about here?
- Mnh-mnh.

08:05.385 --> 08:06.439
Ow!

08:06.463 --> 08:07.738
How long have you had this pain?

08:07.762 --> 08:09.574
A-about a week.

08:09.598 --> 08:10.922
At first, I thought it was just cramps,

08:10.946 --> 08:12.958
but then I got a fever.

08:12.982 --> 08:15.348
Uh, where are your parents? We
need their consent for tests.

08:15.372 --> 08:17.573
My dad's driving in from Dallas.
He had to go there for work.

08:17.597 --> 08:19.259
But you can reach him on his cell.

08:19.294 --> 08:21.899
Does this mean I'm gonna
have to miss volleyball?

08:21.923 --> 08:23.202
I gotta get my practice time.

08:23.226 --> 08:24.580
Uh, what are you in? Eighth grade?

08:24.604 --> 08:26.811
Ninth grade. I'm a freshman.

08:26.835 --> 08:29.296
I play J.V., but I'm
first alternate on varsity.

08:29.566 --> 08:31.775
Wow. Is that how you,
uh, sprained your wrist?

08:31.799 --> 08:33.991
No. Carpal tunnel.

08:34.015 --> 08:35.994
My dad says I text too much.

08:37.296 --> 08:39.611
I-I see you had your appendix taken out.

08:39.645 --> 08:41.851
Yeah, right here.

08:41.885 --> 08:43.140
Still kinda hurts.

08:43.164 --> 08:45.635
Uh, do you remember who your surgeon was?

08:46.660 --> 08:48.422
Dr. Bell-Hart.

08:48.446 --> 08:50.244
- Krista, hold on for a sec.
- Hey.

08:50.268 --> 08:52.736
Hey, I'm doing a surgical
consult on Catherine Redding.

08:52.760 --> 08:54.234
- Uh, she was your...
- My appy patient.

08:54.258 --> 08:56.146
Yeah. She's a sweet
girl. What's she in for?

08:56.170 --> 08:58.504
Abdominal pain and fever. It
could be post-op complications.

08:58.528 --> 09:00.958
- Who was your attending?
- It was Joey, but he let me drive the whole way.

09:00.982 --> 09:03.029
So you counted lap pads?
Irrigated before closing?

09:03.144 --> 09:04.326
You think I screwed up?

09:04.350 --> 09:05.821
You know it could've
been any number of things.

09:05.845 --> 09:06.945
I mean, did you even check?

09:06.969 --> 09:09.535
Of course. I'm still ordering
a C.T. just to be safe.

09:09.789 --> 09:11.580
She's 14 years old,

09:11.613 --> 09:13.248
and you're about to
give her more radiation?

09:13.272 --> 09:16.390
Okay, uh... We'll do an
ultrasound and run labs.

09:16.414 --> 09:17.687
But you better be right,

09:17.711 --> 09:19.181
because if something else happens to her,

09:19.205 --> 09:21.139
this will be on you.

09:23.824 --> 09:25.607
- How's he doing?
- Touch and go.

09:25.630 --> 09:26.888
We stabilized him for surgery.

09:26.912 --> 09:28.836
I heard Scott plowed
into him. Is that true?

09:28.860 --> 09:30.105
Scott doesn't know how it happened.

09:30.129 --> 09:31.664
The police are on their
way. They wanna talk to him.

09:31.688 --> 09:32.838
Oh, that's never good.

09:32.862 --> 09:34.203
Hope for his sake he wasn't responsible.

09:34.227 --> 09:36.306
- Pulse ox is down to 80.
- Okay.

09:36.330 --> 09:37.542
Second tube is in.

09:37.566 --> 09:39.235
Whoa! Geez!

09:39.259 --> 09:40.562
He's gonna bleed out. Give me gloves.

09:40.586 --> 09:42.352
- I'm losing his pulse.
- Heart rate's up to 170.

09:42.376 --> 09:43.782
I'm cracking his chest.

09:47.880 --> 09:50.844
Aorta is clamped. Paddles.

09:50.868 --> 09:53.298
Clear.

09:53.991 --> 09:55.205
Still nothing.

09:55.239 --> 09:56.610
- Increase to 30 Joules.
- Okay.

09:56.634 --> 09:58.818
Ready? Clear.

10:02.919 --> 10:04.614
It's beating. That was close.

10:04.647 --> 10:05.989
Pulse is strong.

10:06.023 --> 10:07.280
Let's pack him, get him up to surgery.

10:07.304 --> 10:09.318
- You want me to scrub in?
- No, I can get started.

10:09.351 --> 10:10.597
All right, now most of all,

10:10.632 --> 10:12.111
I need you to convince the
dad to let Scott up there.

10:12.135 --> 10:14.277
- All right.
- Let me get into it. All right.

10:16.135 --> 10:17.893
All right.

10:17.927 --> 10:19.878
Now we gave him something for the pain.

10:19.902 --> 10:21.172
Okay?

10:21.224 --> 10:23.261
This is for you. Okay.

10:24.807 --> 10:26.629
The quietest I've ever seen him.

10:27.224 --> 10:28.501
How's he doin'?

10:28.525 --> 10:29.707
Well, his hip is healing fine,

10:29.731 --> 10:31.704
but we're having trouble
getting his heart rate down.

10:31.728 --> 10:34.447
Did he have a history with drugs? Alcohol?

10:34.471 --> 10:36.645
Oh. Yeah, he used to drink a ton.

10:36.679 --> 10:38.597
It's the one thing about him that I fixed.

10:38.631 --> 10:40.453
Well, he is quite the character.

10:40.487 --> 10:43.014
Ooh, he talks a lot and flirts,

10:43.047 --> 10:45.054
skirts death on a daily basis.

10:45.078 --> 10:47.344
He's been that way since I've known him.

10:47.368 --> 10:48.960
Yeah? Does he still ride bulls?

10:48.984 --> 10:51.343
Oh. No, not on the rodeo
circuit. They made him quit.

10:51.367 --> 10:52.933
So what does he do in the rodeo?

10:52.967 --> 10:54.694
Nearly gets himself killed.

10:54.727 --> 10:56.710
Steer wrestlin', barrel racin'.

10:56.743 --> 10:58.661
The crowd loves it. We're a team.

10:58.695 --> 11:01.541
I'm retired, but now I call out the acts,

11:01.575 --> 11:03.141
and he does his thing.

11:03.175 --> 11:05.135
- And you're okay with that?
- If you take that away,

11:05.159 --> 11:07.397
he wouldn't be the man I
fell in love with, would he?

11:07.431 --> 11:09.925
Oh, he'd be dead inside without it.

11:09.959 --> 11:11.264
How long have you two been together?

11:11.288 --> 11:13.270
Oh, my goodness.

11:13.294 --> 11:14.908
Too long, I suppose.

11:15.911 --> 11:17.126
Oh, we don't have any rings.

11:17.159 --> 11:18.790
We never thought to make it official.

11:18.823 --> 11:22.373
No kids, though we did talk
about it from time to time.

11:22.407 --> 11:24.509
Seems like a... Sweet guy.

11:24.533 --> 11:26.811
I'm sure he would've been a great dad.

11:28.363 --> 11:30.761
Yeah, his heart's in the right place.

11:30.785 --> 11:33.855
He just never was daddy material.

11:33.879 --> 11:35.830
You know, I'm not the
smartest woman in the world,

11:35.854 --> 11:38.235
but I wasn't dumb enough
to get knocked up by a man

11:38.259 --> 11:42.021
who couldn't think past his next bull ride.

11:44.397 --> 11:45.886
Okay.

11:47.020 --> 11:48.586
E-excuse me.

11:52.418 --> 11:53.664
You almost died out there.

11:53.688 --> 11:55.126
Yeah. It was really
something, huh?

11:55.150 --> 11:56.481
I haven't felt that way since, uh...

11:56.505 --> 11:58.339
Yeah, getting shot at and missed.
It's great.

11:58.363 --> 12:00.025
Kinda makes you see everything
in a whole new light.

12:00.049 --> 12:02.192
Yeah? So what are you seeing?

12:02.216 --> 12:04.618
Aw, you
know, just how confused I am.

12:04.641 --> 12:06.655
You know, my... my life's changing so much.

12:06.679 --> 12:08.597
I feel bad for Jordan.

12:08.621 --> 12:10.507
You know, I just... I feel stupid for...

12:10.531 --> 12:11.900
for holding back, for not going all in.

12:11.924 --> 12:14.130
Oh, no, no. You went all
in. You got her pregnant.

12:14.154 --> 12:15.528
Yeah.

12:15.552 --> 12:17.086
Yeah, but she needs more than that from me.

12:17.110 --> 12:19.539
You know, I thought I'd be
okay by now, but after...

12:19.563 --> 12:21.641
Breakdown in group and...

12:23.191 --> 12:25.732
Look, having a baby is... is great.

12:25.756 --> 12:27.354
It's exciting. I'm excited.

12:27.378 --> 12:28.688
But?

12:28.712 --> 12:30.982
It just feels like I have to
get things together faster.

12:31.006 --> 12:33.134
I mean, I have to I have to be able

12:33.158 --> 12:34.885
to fix things in my head quicker

12:34.918 --> 12:36.543
- than if we weren't having a kid, you know?
- Yeah.

12:36.567 --> 12:38.146
Lot of added pressure.

12:38.170 --> 12:39.862
- Yeah? And what does Jordan have to say?
- I haven't told her.

12:39.886 --> 12:41.562
- Why?
- W-why?

12:41.587 --> 12:42.957
Because I'm...
I don't know what to say.

12:42.981 --> 12:44.557
You know, it's all kinda
swirling around in my head.

12:44.581 --> 12:45.496
And...

12:45.520 --> 12:46.485
You know, I don't wanna hurt her.

12:46.509 --> 12:48.149
I don't want her to feel like
it's anything to do with her,

12:48.173 --> 12:49.778
'cause it's not. It's all me.

12:49.801 --> 12:51.596
- But not telling her's worse.
- Uh...

12:51.620 --> 12:53.282
Dr. Callahan, the patient's ready now.

12:53.863 --> 12:55.621
All right. Patient's ready.

12:55.645 --> 12:56.930
- Lucky you.
- Mm-hmm.

12:56.954 --> 12:58.016
Yeah.

12:58.040 --> 13:00.200
- I got witnesses he hit my boy. Now you're telling me...
- I understand.

13:00.224 --> 13:02.032
- I-I know this is hard, Mr. Johnson.
- That he's the best man for this job?

13:02.056 --> 13:04.196
- You don't know nothin'! What you talking about?
- Look, Dr. Clemmens...

13:04.220 --> 13:07.252
- is our most qualified surgeon, especially with this...
- Mr. Johnson?

13:07.276 --> 13:09.890
- Type of... Scott, this is not a good time.
- What the hell are you doing here?

13:09.914 --> 13:12.085
- Take another step closer!
- Please! If you want your boy to live,

13:12.109 --> 13:13.051
you'll let me do this operation.

13:13.075 --> 13:15.351
- You're not touching my boy.
- Just let me say my piece, please.

13:15.375 --> 13:18.311
Sir, Malik's lung is badly injured,

13:18.335 --> 13:20.349
and several ribs are
detached from his chest.

13:20.373 --> 13:21.616
We need to repair the lung

13:21.640 --> 13:23.365
and put his chest wall back together.

13:23.389 --> 13:25.465
No one can do that like I can.

13:25.582 --> 13:28.106
Believe me, Mr. Johnson, there
is nobody in this hospital...

13:28.130 --> 13:30.464
nobody wants your boy
to live more than I do.

13:30.488 --> 13:31.549
Oh, is that right?

13:31.573 --> 13:33.987
More than me? More than his family?

13:34.011 --> 13:36.310
- No, what I meant...
- I know what you meant!

13:36.334 --> 13:39.322
You meant that you're guilty. You hit him.

13:39.346 --> 13:42.200
So you go in there and
you better go fix my boy.

13:42.224 --> 13:44.896
That's right, 'cause if you
don't, I'm gonna sue you,

13:44.920 --> 13:46.582
and I'm gonna see your ass rot in jail.

13:46.606 --> 13:47.885
Okay, we'll fix it.

13:47.909 --> 13:49.987
Okay, go scrub in for
surgery. I'll call legal.

13:50.011 --> 13:51.193
Yeah.

13:52.571 --> 13:54.665
Don't say nothin' to me!
Don't say nothin' to me.

14:01.541 --> 14:03.562
All right.

14:03.586 --> 14:05.575
No sign of gallstones. Could be viral.

14:05.599 --> 14:07.005
Or a
drug-resistant peritonitis.

14:07.029 --> 14:08.452
Did you sterilize your instruments?

14:08.476 --> 14:09.770
No, I spat on them Paul. What do you think?

14:09.794 --> 14:11.403
I think there's a giant neon
sign on this girl that says

14:11.427 --> 14:13.921
- mistakes were made during surgery.
- Oh, a few weeks into your rotation,

14:13.945 --> 14:15.689
you're suddenly the expert
on surgical mistakes.

14:15.713 --> 14:17.847
- You're not your dad.
- Gee, thank you for the reminder.

14:17.871 --> 14:19.245
You know, maybe if you
focused more on surgery

14:19.269 --> 14:20.559
a little bit more than Joey's ass,

14:20.583 --> 14:21.964
- this girl wouldn't be back in here.
- You don't...

14:21.988 --> 14:23.147
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
I get this crap at home.

14:23.171 --> 14:25.089
I don't need it here.
What the hell's going on?

14:25.113 --> 14:27.379
We were just... disagreeing
on the differential.

14:27.403 --> 14:29.528
You guys are on the same team.

14:29.698 --> 14:31.734
Sorry. We... we'll work together.

14:31.758 --> 14:32.884
See that you do.

14:32.908 --> 14:35.248
Just run your tests and
then report back to me.

14:35.272 --> 14:37.112
- All right. Thank you. Thank you.
- All right.

14:37.305 --> 14:38.552
Nice job.

14:38.576 --> 14:40.034
Really? You're blaming me?

14:40.058 --> 14:41.880
- Yeah.
- Yeah, don't worry. I'll solve this.

14:41.904 --> 14:43.534
Right.

14:43.808 --> 14:45.607
Any word on Scott?

14:45.631 --> 14:47.736
Okay, the rumor mill? It is in full force.

14:47.760 --> 14:48.927
Yeah. You know, was it his fault?

14:48.951 --> 14:50.165
- Wasn't it his fault?
- Right.

14:50.189 --> 14:51.499
I can't imagine what he's going through.

14:51.523 --> 14:53.793
Yeah, my buddy on the force
said he might be facing charges.

14:53.817 --> 14:54.958
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

14:54.982 --> 14:56.303
- Hey, I'll see you later?
- Yeah.

14:56.735 --> 14:58.008
- Jordan.
- Yeah?

14:58.032 --> 14:59.941
Fresh off the scan Shane's heart echo.

14:59.965 --> 15:02.317
- It's weird. His ejection fraction is way down.
- Hello, ma'am.

15:02.341 --> 15:04.475
- I'm Dr. Beckman.
- You think this is weird? Look at that.

15:04.498 --> 15:06.999
I hate to be the one to
deliver this news to you, ma'am,

15:07.023 --> 15:09.261
but you have lupus, and...

15:09.285 --> 15:11.105
- Maybe the herpes.
- Shane?

15:11.129 --> 15:13.540
- I'm here for my bunion.
- I understand, ma'am.

15:13.564 --> 15:15.511
- Shane, what is going on?
- I'm sorry. He's not a doctor. I apologize.

15:15.535 --> 15:16.878
What do you mean I'm not a doctor?

15:16.902 --> 15:19.331
- You don't think I know who I am?
- Baby, this is not funny.

15:19.355 --> 15:21.756
- Yeah, stop fooling around.
- No, but my name's Dr. Beckman.

15:22.214 --> 15:23.797
- I sincerely apologize.
- And this... this... this woman here,

15:23.821 --> 15:25.933
she's in serious troub...

15:25.956 --> 15:28.585
- Let's get you back... Drew!
- Oh, my God!

15:30.669 --> 15:32.091
- Baby!
- Let's get him on his side.

15:32.115 --> 15:33.088
Shane!

15:33.112 --> 15:35.384
Somebody get a gurney, please.

15:35.408 --> 15:37.508
You gotta help him!

15:40.449 --> 15:42.207
Okay.

15:42.539 --> 15:44.265
You see there?

15:44.289 --> 15:46.751
Now Shane's bleeding is caused
by dilated veins in his throat

15:46.786 --> 15:48.319
called varices.

15:48.343 --> 15:50.512
They can be caused by alcoholism.

15:50.536 --> 15:53.248
It is possible that he
never stopped drinking?

15:53.665 --> 15:54.816
No, I believe he quit.

15:54.849 --> 15:57.055
I mean, he makes things
up, but he's not a liar.

15:57.090 --> 15:59.391
Well, did he ever have
a psychiatric evaluation?

15:59.425 --> 16:01.055
No. Not since I've known him.

16:01.089 --> 16:03.231
- Okay.
- Listen, I know how people talk,

16:03.265 --> 16:04.585
and I know that he can be boastful,

16:04.609 --> 16:05.919
but that is...

16:05.953 --> 16:08.447
That's just part of being
in the rodeo, you know?

16:08.481 --> 16:11.103
And stretching the truth's
just part of the charm.

16:11.138 --> 16:12.895
Well...

16:12.929 --> 16:16.831
Pretending to be a doctor
is a step beyond boastful.

16:16.865 --> 16:19.615
Yeah. That did kind of freak me out.

16:19.649 --> 16:21.215
Yeah. You just hang tight, okay?

16:23.169 --> 16:26.559
Wait, in... in which case,
liability is <i> unlimited?</i>

16:26.593 --> 16:27.904
That...

16:27.927 --> 16:29.398
Hold... hold on a second.

16:29.441 --> 16:31.049
- What is it, Michael?
- You have visitors.

16:31.073 --> 16:32.932
They say they've been waiting a long time.

16:32.956 --> 16:34.825
Greg, I gotta... I gotta
call you back. Okay.

16:36.129 --> 16:38.197
- They want more than a drug test, don't they?
- Yeah.

16:38.221 --> 16:40.362
And I overheard them talking
about pressing charges

16:40.386 --> 16:41.632
for reckless driving.

16:43.183 --> 16:45.129
Okay. Uh... stall them.

16:45.153 --> 16:46.879
What? What do you mean "stall them"?

16:46.913 --> 16:48.639
- What do I say?
- Tell them the truth.

16:48.673 --> 16:51.034
Tell them the kid is critical,
and I'm talking to Scott now.

16:56.769 --> 16:58.751
Pulse ox is holding at 91%.

16:58.785 --> 17:00.127
Fine job stopping the bleeding.

17:00.161 --> 17:02.112
Had to take out half a lung to do it.

17:02.145 --> 17:03.425
Stabilize the rib while I drill?

17:03.457 --> 17:05.535
Yeah. Go ahead.

17:07.800 --> 17:09.780
Guy, I hate to have to do this.

17:09.804 --> 17:11.368
Scott, I need you to
come downstairs with me.

17:11.393 --> 17:13.294
- You gotta be kidding me.
- What the hell's going on?

17:13.318 --> 17:14.696
Tee, please just take over.

17:14.721 --> 17:17.119
Are you insane? The boy
has a hole in his chest.

17:17.153 --> 17:19.565
Y-you think I wanna do this?
The police are downstairs.

17:19.589 --> 17:20.719
Well, the police can wait.

17:20.742 --> 17:22.232
Let me give you a reality check, Scott.

17:22.256 --> 17:24.430
They're talking about
filing charges down there.

17:24.637 --> 17:26.715
That's right. Take the damn drug test.

17:26.740 --> 17:28.905
No, I'm not leaving the
kid. We need one more hour,

17:28.929 --> 17:30.089
and then they can do what they want.

17:30.113 --> 17:31.965
- Give him the hour, Toph.
- One hour.

17:31.989 --> 17:34.324
I don't know that I can, but I'll try.

17:34.529 --> 17:35.807
You okay?

17:35.841 --> 17:38.143
Do I have a choice?

17:38.177 --> 17:39.327
Stabilize the rib.

17:39.361 --> 17:40.770
Got it.

17:44.449 --> 17:46.335
You really cried watching "Finding Nemo"?

17:46.369 --> 17:48.831
Oh, my God. Like a freakin' baby.

17:48.865 --> 17:51.231
I mean, his mom gets
killed the first minute.

17:51.265 --> 17:53.695
Are you serious? Who put
that in a kid's movie?

17:53.729 --> 17:56.041
I'm freakin' almost tearing
up thinking about it right now.

17:56.065 --> 17:57.567
Stupid-ass barracuda.

17:57.601 --> 17:59.071
I was surprised it got you.

17:59.105 --> 18:01.631
Why do you always say stuff like that?

18:01.665 --> 18:02.751
Like what?

18:02.785 --> 18:04.799
Like you're always
surprised that I feel this

18:04.833 --> 18:06.047
or that I feel...

18:06.081 --> 18:07.583
Basically, that I show my feelings.

18:07.617 --> 18:09.929
- That I'm open.
- I... I'm just giving you crap. Whatever.

18:09.953 --> 18:11.369
You're a guy. I'm not
used to that from guys.

18:11.393 --> 18:13.024
Okay, what are you used to in guys?

18:13.048 --> 18:15.593
Well, you know that I've dated,
like, 10,000, so let me see...

18:15.617 --> 18:18.015
Ahh. There we go. I
remember this.

18:18.049 --> 18:20.511
We're deflecting again.
You know, you do that a lot.

18:20.545 --> 18:23.037
Okay, so I'm always...

18:23.061 --> 18:25.171
Surprised by you and I always deflect.

18:25.195 --> 18:27.213
Is there anything else
you'd like to comment on?

18:27.237 --> 18:29.347
Look, I'm not putting you
down. We're just talking.

18:29.371 --> 18:31.529
Mm-hmm. We just... we're
having casual conversation.

18:31.553 --> 18:32.830
Yo, listen, I-I deflect, too.

18:32.854 --> 18:35.625
I-I have the fake laugh I
do when I don't wanna talk.

18:35.649 --> 18:37.023
You know what I'm talking
about, when I don't want to talk.

18:37.047 --> 18:39.509
No, that's... I-it's not
that I don't wanna talk.

18:39.533 --> 18:40.683
It's just, I don't want to talk about that.

18:40.707 --> 18:43.073
The men in my past? No, don't do that.

18:44.783 --> 18:45.934
Okay.

18:45.958 --> 18:47.733
We'll... we'll talk about something else.

18:47.756 --> 18:49.811
We're here.

18:52.833 --> 18:55.167
Ow! My back! Oh, my God!

18:55.201 --> 18:56.806
- My back! My back!
- Make room here.

18:56.830 --> 18:58.375
- Oh! Oh! Ah!
- All right, everybody, back up.

18:58.399 --> 19:00.025
I fell off the roof. There's no railing.

19:00.048 --> 19:01.767
Okay, let me go get the backboard.

19:01.791 --> 19:02.877
- And get me a painkiller!
- Yep.

19:02.901 --> 19:04.389
Hold up. Hold up. Hold on.

19:04.413 --> 19:07.131
Okay, who saw this man fall?

19:07.155 --> 19:08.497
Anybody?

19:08.521 --> 19:09.735
Uh...

19:09.759 --> 19:12.092
Who... who actually saw it??

19:12.116 --> 19:14.290
You? You didn't see anything, huh?

19:14.314 --> 19:16.284
No. I didn't think so.

19:16.672 --> 19:18.335
Get the hell up.

19:18.369 --> 19:20.287
I-I can't even move, man.

19:20.311 --> 19:21.302
I can't move.

19:21.326 --> 19:22.667
Get up, Sean.

19:22.691 --> 19:24.118
Wait. You know him?

19:24.141 --> 19:25.643
Oh, yeah. Oh, yeah.

19:25.667 --> 19:27.810
Every come of months, he
takes a ride to the E.R.

19:27.834 --> 19:31.096
And every time, it's the same
story... fell off the roof.

19:31.120 --> 19:32.745
And every time, he just wants more Oxy.

19:34.209 --> 19:35.359
Come on. On your feet, Sean.

19:35.393 --> 19:38.655
Aw, man! Yeah. There we go.

19:38.689 --> 19:40.959
Come on, Kenny. Damn, man.

19:40.993 --> 19:43.807
Aw, man. That sucks, huh?

19:43.841 --> 19:45.919
Have a nice night.

19:45.953 --> 19:47.327
Nicely done.

19:47.361 --> 19:49.785
I got a few moves.

19:58.793 --> 20:00.250
- Uh, look, Krista...
- You know what?

20:00.274 --> 20:01.410
I-I don't think we should
talk about anything

20:01.434 --> 20:02.580
other than the case right now, Paul.

20:02.604 --> 20:04.631
Okay. All right. Well, um...

20:04.655 --> 20:06.532
Let's, uh, review what we have here.

20:06.556 --> 20:08.222
It's a weird collection of symptoms.

20:08.246 --> 20:09.210
Uh, inflamed pancreas.

20:09.234 --> 20:10.504
Pleural effusions.

20:10.528 --> 20:11.654
Trouble breathing.

20:11.678 --> 20:13.049
Increasing pain.

20:13.172 --> 20:14.652
All in a 14-year-old girl.

20:20.409 --> 20:21.696
Catherine's on the J.V. squad, right?

20:21.720 --> 20:22.814
Uh, yeah.

20:22.838 --> 20:25.123
But she's pissed she's not on varsity.

20:25.147 --> 20:26.467
And she wants a scholarship to college.

20:26.491 --> 20:28.390
I mean, what if she's
trying to impress her dad?

20:28.623 --> 20:31.004
Yeah. It wouldn't be the first time.

20:31.039 --> 20:32.776
That's our answer.

20:32.811 --> 20:35.485
Her carpal tunnel isn't
from texting, is it?

20:35.509 --> 20:36.732
We need a hormone panel.

20:36.756 --> 20:38.671
Yeah. Come on.

20:38.695 --> 20:40.410
Let me make this as clear as I can.

20:40.434 --> 20:42.741
If you pull Scott
Clemmens from this surgery,

20:42.765 --> 20:44.245
you are endangering this boy's life.

20:44.271 --> 20:45.944
We were told there's
another doctor up there.

20:45.968 --> 20:47.245
You're a doctor. You can replace him.

20:47.269 --> 20:48.497
No, it doesn't work that way.

20:48.531 --> 20:50.236
Scott Clemmens is our on-call surgeon.

20:50.271 --> 20:51.429
I just spoke with Scott.

20:51.462 --> 20:52.985
They just need one more hour up there.

20:53.009 --> 20:54.360
They have a warrant, Topher.

20:54.394 --> 20:55.723
We just got a bystander
video from the accident.

20:55.747 --> 20:57.678
This will change your mind.

21:04.670 --> 21:07.825
He ran right through that stop sign.

21:11.403 --> 21:13.560
B.P.'s down to 74 systolic.

21:13.594 --> 21:14.784
Something's wrong.

21:14.818 --> 21:16.491
It's not just a bleed.

21:16.525 --> 21:17.876
Scott, we got company.

21:17.910 --> 21:19.326
Guys, I did what I could.

21:19.360 --> 21:20.623
I said we needed more time.

21:20.647 --> 21:22.642
They have you on video, Scott.

21:23.881 --> 21:26.272
Scott Clemmens. San Antonio Police.

21:26.296 --> 21:27.696
You need to come with us right now.

21:38.027 --> 21:39.314
I'll be back.

21:39.349 --> 21:40.507
Okay. Yeah.

