- I'm trying.

21:54.406 --> 21:58.073
There she is. My wild Texas Rose.

21:58.097 --> 22:00.608
Hi, Shane. How you feeling?

22:00.633 --> 22:02.905
He's gettin' weaker. I
never seen him this bad.

22:02.929 --> 22:06.181
I'm all stove up, ready for the big dance.

22:06.216 --> 22:07.631
Shane, don't talk like that.

22:07.665 --> 22:10.176
I been ready for some
time, baby. You know that.

22:10.210 --> 22:12.173
I'm at peace with the world.

22:12.207 --> 22:14.782
That's the delusions talking, isn't it?

22:14.816 --> 22:16.772
Doctor, isn't it?

22:17.104 --> 22:18.390
Please tell me that it is.

22:18.425 --> 22:21.096
I'm sorry. We have a few more
tests that we need to run.

22:21.130 --> 22:23.480
Um... Drew, can I speak with you outside?

22:23.514 --> 22:25.188
Yeah. Excuse me.

22:29.023 --> 22:31.437
I put in a swan. He's got a
little upper cardiac failure.

22:31.471 --> 22:32.790
I couldn't figure out the cause.

22:32.824 --> 22:34.530
Okay, what about the psychotic behavior?

22:34.556 --> 22:37.260
Comes and goes. Two minutes
ago, he was a Navy S.E.A.L.

22:37.302 --> 22:39.082
But it's weird 'cause he keeps
telling the same rodeo story,

22:39.106 --> 22:40.757
but it's got different
people in it each time.

22:40.781 --> 22:42.326
All right, let's run another scan.

22:42.360 --> 22:43.656
And could you please bring Lindsay out?

22:43.680 --> 22:44.849
I need to talk to her in private.

22:44.873 --> 22:46.223
- Yeah. Okay.
- Thank you.

22:50.896 --> 22:52.408
Any news from T.C.?

22:52.443 --> 22:54.323
Yeah, he's still in
surgery. Topher's assisting.

22:55.171 --> 22:56.550
How you holding up?

22:56.574 --> 22:58.153
How do you think I'm holding up, Michael?

22:58.177 --> 22:59.431
I'm getting drug tested.

22:59.465 --> 23:01.645
I didn't use anything. I didn't drink.

23:01.669 --> 23:03.439
Okay. Come on, let's have a seat.

23:07.969 --> 23:11.640
Okay.

23:13.703 --> 23:16.690
Did you... tell them what happened?

23:16.714 --> 23:19.838
Yes. Ten times.

23:20.114 --> 23:22.271
I was driving to the
clinic. I was running late.

23:22.304 --> 23:24.912
I looked down for, like, 2
seconds.<i> Maybe</i> 2 seconds.

23:24.946 --> 23:26.168
And the next thing I know,

23:26.203 --> 23:28.134
this kid's car is right in front of me.

23:30.069 --> 23:31.806
If anything happens to him...

23:31.840 --> 23:35.350
No, no, no, no, no.
Come on. We won't let it.

23:43.179 --> 23:45.272
Aren't we a mess tonight?

23:45.305 --> 23:46.850
Yeah.

23:46.884 --> 23:48.364
Yeah.

23:48.398 --> 23:49.501
How about this? How about this?

23:49.525 --> 23:51.338
How about we move away
from the awkward silences

23:51.362 --> 23:54.452
and, uh, try to guess what
the other person is feeling?

23:54.487 --> 23:56.192
Um...

23:56.226 --> 23:59.123
Give me a little space here.

24:02.573 --> 24:04.535
How about we talk about something

24:04.569 --> 24:06.733
that's really been bothering me?

24:06.757 --> 24:08.759
W-what?

24:10.817 --> 24:12.524
How gassy you are when you sleep.

24:14.620 --> 24:15.939
- I mean...
- I'm not gassy!

24:15.973 --> 24:17.592
I mean, but I didn't want
to say anything before,

24:17.616 --> 24:18.881
but it's like we've reached this point now

24:18.905 --> 24:20.523
- where I feel that we can talk about these things.
- No.

24:20.547 --> 24:21.716
We're at a plateau. Oh, my God.

24:21.740 --> 24:23.767
We can... we can
talk about these things.

24:23.793 --> 24:26.529
- I'm not!
- Uh, yes, you are. I mean, you done woke...

24:26.572 --> 24:29.466
- No, I'm not!
- You done woke me up outta some deep, sound sleep.

24:29.490 --> 24:32.475
- You are making this up!
- Dream state, okay?

24:32.499 --> 24:34.075
But I...

24:34.099 --> 24:35.342
Would... would I lie about
something this serious?

24:35.366 --> 24:37.356
- Unh-unh. Yes.
- I mean, this is a serious issue.

24:37.380 --> 24:38.667
Oh. Baby, it's like...

24:38.691 --> 24:40.268
it's like you're in a
hot... we're in a hotbox.

24:40.292 --> 24:42.642
It's like I'm in
a it's like I'm in a hotbox.

24:42.666 --> 24:45.682
- Is it a nice hotbox?
- I mean, it's like you got the child lock going.

24:45.706 --> 24:47.219
- I can't get out.
- You poor thing.

24:47.253 --> 24:48.128
I don't know where to go.

24:48.152 --> 24:49.600
I don't wanna go nowhere.
That's the important thing.

24:49.624 --> 24:51.265
I don't even wanna go nowhere.

24:51.289 --> 24:53.271
Gwen, we got a code 3 for chest pain.

24:53.296 --> 24:54.743
But, yeah,
we'll finish this later.

24:54.767 --> 24:56.376
- Oh, yes, we will.
- We're gonna finish it.

24:56.400 --> 24:58.378
The morning trumpets will be talked about.

25:02.540 --> 25:04.928
Okay, Shane's heart is
not pumping enough blood,

25:04.953 --> 25:06.754
and we're trying to figure out why.

25:06.778 --> 25:10.351
Has he had any mental changes before this?

25:10.375 --> 25:12.370
Oh, well, little slips here and there.

25:12.394 --> 25:14.488
I-I was afraid it might be Alzheimer's.

25:14.512 --> 25:17.023
Mm. Those are called confabulations.

25:17.047 --> 25:20.405
See, he's not forgetting.
He's making things up.

25:20.429 --> 25:22.482
You know, about his past, who he is.

25:22.506 --> 25:24.663
Might that have something
to do with his disease?

25:24.687 --> 25:25.959
It might.

25:25.983 --> 25:27.975
I know that he's had problems with alcohol,

25:27.999 --> 25:30.123
but... What about this diet?

25:30.147 --> 25:31.950
Shane is all about the protein.

25:32.036 --> 25:33.936
Rice and shrimp.

25:37.332 --> 25:38.972
Rice and shrimp and...

25:38.996 --> 25:40.084
That's it.

25:40.109 --> 25:42.889
No fruits or vegetables? Other meats?

25:42.913 --> 25:44.712
- Dairy?
- Oh! No. No.

25:44.736 --> 25:46.726
He hates greens. He's lactose-intolerant.

25:46.750 --> 25:48.034
But he love shrimp.

25:49.721 --> 25:51.231
Why? Does that mean something?

25:51.291 --> 25:53.701
You know, it just might. Um...

25:53.930 --> 25:55.986
I'm sorry. You'll have to excuse me.

26:02.694 --> 26:03.818
Hey.

26:04.807 --> 26:06.853
I'm Michael Ragosa.

26:06.877 --> 26:09.490
- Yeah, I thought I'd bring you s...
- How's Malik?

26:11.233 --> 26:13.962
He's, uh, he's still in critical condition.

26:17.929 --> 26:20.721
- But he's alive?
- Yeah.

26:20.970 --> 26:22.547
Yeah, we're doing everything we can.

26:22.572 --> 26:24.988
The damage to the lungs
was much more extensive

26:25.012 --> 26:26.135
than we thought.

26:26.169 --> 26:27.839
But Dr. Clemmens is gonna fix him, right?

26:29.228 --> 26:30.930
He's in good hands.

26:34.605 --> 26:38.204
My boy Malik is special.

26:38.411 --> 26:40.255
Now I know every parent
says that about their kid,

26:40.279 --> 26:41.341
but...

26:41.365 --> 26:43.701
Man, he's got something extra.

26:43.857 --> 26:45.418
I mean, I knew that since the first day

26:45.442 --> 26:47.047
I saw his big hands when he was born.

26:48.251 --> 26:49.502
He's a musician.

26:49.526 --> 26:50.638
Really?

26:50.662 --> 26:52.429
Oh, yeah. Yeah. Uh, matter of fact...

26:52.453 --> 26:53.817
Check this out.

26:57.175 --> 26:59.578
- Ahh. All right. It's really good.
- Yeah!

26:59.602 --> 27:01.209
And all the instruments, that's him.

27:01.233 --> 27:03.128
Piano, guitar, that's all him.

27:03.152 --> 27:05.074
- Right.
- I mean, that's just him just messin' around.

27:05.098 --> 27:06.960
I mean, he's been like
that ever since he was 5.

27:06.984 --> 27:09.426
- Wow.
- Man, he's got a bright future.

27:10.915 --> 27:12.913
Brighter than I ever had.

27:16.358 --> 27:19.120
Why my son?

27:19.169 --> 27:21.008
Why my boy?

27:21.032 --> 27:22.445
I wish I knew.

27:30.946 --> 27:32.520
What'd you guys find?

27:32.544 --> 27:34.149
We tested your blood for hormone levels.

27:34.173 --> 27:36.678
We found high levels of growth hormones.

27:36.703 --> 27:37.729
Dangerously high.

27:37.753 --> 27:40.323
Catherine, you need to stop using it.

27:40.347 --> 27:41.696
It's killing you.

27:41.720 --> 27:43.680
You don't understand what it's like,

27:43.704 --> 27:45.290
trying to compete.

27:45.314 --> 27:47.024
If I stop now, I'm gone.

27:47.048 --> 27:50.068
No varsity team. No scholarship.

27:50.215 --> 27:52.655
That was
our whole plan. It...

27:52.679 --> 27:54.828
oh, my God.

27:55.375 --> 27:57.142
That's my dad. What am I gonna tell him?

27:57.166 --> 27:59.222
The truth. He's going to hear it from us.

27:59.246 --> 28:01.495
It's probably better if
he hears it from you first.

28:01.519 --> 28:03.028
So, how she doing?

28:03.052 --> 28:05.435
Uh, we'll let her tell you.

28:05.459 --> 28:07.271
I put a rush on Scott's blood test.

28:07.295 --> 28:09.476
- Well, how long?
- Not sure.

28:09.500 --> 28:11.781
Maybe an hour? I don't
think he has an hour.

28:11.805 --> 28:14.914
I mean, I can do it, but
I'm not as fast as Scott.

28:14.938 --> 28:17.225
We gotta do something. This
kid's not gonna make it.

28:17.249 --> 28:19.805
I have an idea. Let me go talk to Jordan.

28:19.829 --> 28:21.386
All right.

28:25.853 --> 28:27.300
- What's going on?
- Hey.

28:27.324 --> 28:28.489
I'm gonna ask you this once,

28:28.513 --> 28:29.935
and you are gonna tell me the truth.

28:29.959 --> 28:31.115
- Understand?
- We were...

28:31.139 --> 28:33.428
And I know what your mother means to you,

28:33.452 --> 28:36.409
so you swear on her life
that you did not have a drink

28:36.433 --> 28:37.781
or take anything.

28:37.805 --> 28:40.504
Jordan, you know that I haven't
had a drink in over 10 years.

28:40.528 --> 28:42.891
- I still go to meetings.
- Swear that when those results come back,

28:42.915 --> 28:44.562
- they will be negative.
- I swear.

28:44.586 --> 28:45.581
- For anything.
- Yes.

28:45.605 --> 28:48.046
- On your mother.
- On... My... Mother.

28:48.070 --> 28:49.342
What are you talking about?

28:49.659 --> 28:51.231
I'm talking about

28:51.256 --> 28:53.246
your test results will
take another 45 minutes...

28:53.270 --> 28:55.422
And Malik
does not have that time.

28:55.446 --> 28:58.305
So we are signing off on the results.

29:02.586 --> 29:04.417
You're you're faking them?

29:04.441 --> 29:07.365
No. We're just saying
that they're negative,

29:07.389 --> 29:10.450
which means we are all
going out on a limb for you.

29:10.474 --> 29:12.819
So I need to know that I can trust you

29:12.843 --> 29:15.983
when you say that those results
will be clean as a whistle.

29:16.007 --> 29:18.584
Because that's what
they're going to be, right?

29:21.294 --> 29:24.366
Yes. They will.

29:24.677 --> 29:26.443
Okay.

29:27.826 --> 29:29.857
All right.

29:37.902 --> 29:40.023
Heart's tachy to 158.

29:40.047 --> 29:41.781
B.P. only 64.

29:41.805 --> 29:43.379
You were right.
It's an air embolism.

29:43.403 --> 29:44.558
Yeah, already in the heart.

29:44.582 --> 29:46.353
That bubble reaches the
kid's coronary, he's dead.

29:46.377 --> 29:47.951
Increase OÂ² to 100%.

29:48.715 --> 29:50.610
- I'm losing his pulse.
- Damn it.

29:50.634 --> 29:52.784
Okay, I can try to aspirate
the air from the atrium.

29:52.808 --> 29:54.147
But, uh, let's place the central line.

29:54.171 --> 29:56.796
No time for that. He'll be dead by then.

29:56.820 --> 29:57.879
So what do we do?

29:57.903 --> 29:59.187
We take it directly out of the heart.

29:59.211 --> 30:00.463
Have you done this before?

30:00.487 --> 30:03.181
Yes. Only about a dozen times.

30:11.405 --> 30:12.594
There is the embolism.

30:13.242 --> 30:14.247
You got it.

30:14.506 --> 30:17.013
Okay, this is Thiamine, or Vitamin B.

30:17.037 --> 30:18.797
Now your body doesn't have enough of it,

30:18.821 --> 30:20.543
and it hasn't in a long time.

30:20.567 --> 30:21.787
Okay, let's get your over on your side.

30:21.811 --> 30:23.397
Wait. That... that's it? A vitamin?

30:23.421 --> 30:26.151
Well, the deficiency has caused
Shane to suffer an illness

30:26.175 --> 30:27.702
called Korsakoff Psychosis.

30:27.727 --> 30:29.878
Now if severe,

30:29.903 --> 30:31.475
it can really mess with your heart.

30:31.499 --> 30:33.733
That and, well, you make things up.

30:33.757 --> 30:35.863
What are you talking about?
She's calling me a liar.

30:35.887 --> 30:37.511
You are one, Shane.

30:37.535 --> 30:39.864
Aah! Jesus!

30:39.888 --> 30:42.751
The good news is, it's reversible, okay.

30:42.775 --> 30:45.393
Regular Thiamine and a
diet other than just shrimp,

30:45.417 --> 30:47.674
and... No alcohol.

30:47.698 --> 30:51.779
A-alcohol? No, I-I, uh, I
don't take the drink. No, uh...

30:51.803 --> 30:54.397
- I know you tried, honey.
- I'm sorry.

30:54.421 --> 30:56.891
I think the best thing for Shane
right now would be some rest.

30:56.915 --> 30:58.391
I used to like you.

30:58.426 --> 31:00.449
All right.

31:04.942 --> 31:07.351
So the stories are gonna stop?

31:07.375 --> 31:09.430
No, his behavior won't stop right away.

31:09.454 --> 31:11.027
It might take a few months to clear up.

31:11.052 --> 31:12.400
And the thrill-seekin'?

31:12.424 --> 31:14.685
The risk-taking can be
part of the condition.

31:14.709 --> 31:16.408
Yeah, but that's who he is.

31:16.432 --> 31:18.026
He can't lose that light, can he?

31:18.050 --> 31:18.961
I don't know.

31:18.986 --> 31:21.358
I guess you're gonna find
out what was really Shane

31:21.382 --> 31:23.435
and what wasn't.

31:25.742 --> 31:26.897
Hey.

31:29.323 --> 31:31.528
Did you ever try to change him?

31:31.688 --> 31:34.282
Sure. In the beginning.

31:34.306 --> 31:35.815
But you know what?

31:35.850 --> 31:38.680
Eventually, you realize that
you love a man for his falls

31:38.704 --> 31:40.374
as much as his wins.

31:41.036 --> 31:42.812
Maybe even more.

31:45.194 --> 31:47.217
Yeah.

31:47.241 --> 31:48.751
It's complicated, isn't it?

31:48.775 --> 31:49.899
Mm-hmm.

31:49.923 --> 31:50.923
Mm-hmm.

31:55.719 --> 31:57.035
Hey, great save, Scott.

31:57.070 --> 31:58.836
Yeah. It was touch and go there.

31:58.870 --> 32:00.989
Yeah. Thanks for sticking up for me,

32:01.024 --> 32:02.468
accelerating those test results.

32:02.503 --> 32:04.527
You realize if you were lying...

32:04.560 --> 32:06.487
And something shows up... I wasn't lying.

32:06.521 --> 32:07.976
I'm gonna follow him down to post-op,

32:08.000 --> 32:09.133
make sure everything goes right.

32:09.157 --> 32:10.667
Okay.

32:11.987 --> 32:14.043
Wait, wait, wait! Wait! Wait! Wait! Stop!

32:14.977 --> 32:16.872
- Hey.
- Hi.

32:16.906 --> 32:19.252
So I saw Malik on the way to post-op.

32:19.286 --> 32:21.191
Looks like things went well.

32:21.371 --> 32:24.084
We'll see. Still not out of the woods.

32:24.108 --> 32:26.454
Yeah.

32:28.900 --> 32:30.957
I got your test results back.

32:33.082 --> 32:34.431
Totally clean.

32:35.060 --> 32:37.278
I told you.

32:37.468 --> 32:39.654
Look, I'm...

32:39.997 --> 32:42.311
I should've known that
you wouldn't lie to me,

32:42.346 --> 32:43.907
and I am sorry that I questioned you.

32:43.931 --> 32:44.959
You had to.

32:46.407 --> 32:47.756
But you stood by me.

32:47.780 --> 32:49.636
Yeah.

32:49.660 --> 32:51.427
You know, you stood by me enough.

32:51.451 --> 32:52.818
It's my turn.

33:14.265 --> 33:16.258
I'd say that was a success.

33:16.307 --> 33:17.537
Yeah, but I don't know

33:17.561 --> 33:18.717
if Catherine's gonna see it the same way.

33:18.741 --> 33:20.717
Her volleyball ambitions took a big hit.

33:20.742 --> 33:22.743
Well, as my father likes to say,

33:22.767 --> 33:24.985
life's full is sacrifices. Choose wisely.

33:25.224 --> 33:26.381
Um... Speaking of which,

33:26.405 --> 33:28.528
I just... I-I just wanna say I'm sorry

33:28.552 --> 33:30.706
about what I said earlier. Everything.

33:30.730 --> 33:32.576
I'm just...

33:32.892 --> 33:34.112
I'm competitive.

33:34.136 --> 33:36.915
Like, overly competitive.

33:38.119 --> 33:39.212
And I really wanna be chief resident

33:39.236 --> 33:40.424
in a couple years.

33:40.728 --> 33:42.411
Yeah, we both do.

33:44.870 --> 33:46.749
I-I don't want us to hate each other.

33:46.773 --> 33:48.605
Yeah, me, neither.

33:49.666 --> 33:51.981
We both went mean pretty quickly.

33:52.005 --> 33:53.531
We just have to find a way to stay friends

33:53.555 --> 33:55.012
during all of this, you know?

33:55.036 --> 33:56.450
Yeah, we do.

33:58.325 --> 34:00.414
So I guess we'll, uh, see how it goes then?

34:03.053 --> 34:04.112
Guess so.

34:04.185 --> 34:06.274
Okay.

34:15.360 --> 34:17.835
He should be coming out of
anesthesia any minute now.

34:17.860 --> 34:19.531
There you go.

34:19.554 --> 34:20.679
We got movement.

34:23.984 --> 34:25.462
Okay, Malik.

34:27.953 --> 34:30.235
Good.

34:30.585 --> 34:32.353
Pupils are reactive.

34:32.377 --> 34:35.929
There he is. That's my boy. Oh, thank God.

34:35.954 --> 34:38.590
Okay, Malik, I'm going to
ask you a few questions.

34:38.614 --> 34:40.002
I don't want to try and speak yet,

34:40.025 --> 34:43.563
